history.text: The metacritic score seems lower than I expected.
Hello!  Have you seen The Avengers?
Yeah I've seen it 3 times.
Have you seen it?
Yes I have seen it a few times.
Did you like it?
Who was your favorite character?
Yeah I think it was a good introduction to the series I like the movies in general.
I'd say captain America is my favorite.
Who is your favorite character?
I agree with you that the metacritic score seemed low.
Iron Man is my favorite.  He's so snarky and jerkish.
Yeah I think Robert Downey Jr. was the perfect actor for Tony Stark
I think the key scene is the only thing different on the document doesn't seem like we got much new info to talk about.
That is true lol
By the way are you h uman?
I am

I suppose we might as well talk about the new info then, I think I would have preferred
 a different plot unrelated to loki for the first movie what about you?
Yes I thought that was an odd way to start the series.
The new stuff reminds me I don't think I can remember the hulk doing anything in the series except going on a rampage you'd think they'd have kicked him out by now.
He is boring.
He's always getting made and Romanoff has to calm him down.
Yeah can't really have good writing when it comes to a mindless killing machine.
I think how this works is we need to respond to eachother for it to count so you probably have to say something after I do to keep this moving.
The Tesseract was so out there.  So unrealistic.
Yeah didn't feel like a good plot point at all, I think they should have started with the infinity gauntlet stuff.
In the next scene the angry hulk actually does something good
Being angry pays off
Yeah it was about the only scene in the series I think I liked the hulk.
The missle was a good climax atleast for the movie with IronMan potentially having to sacrifice himself.
Yes.  I didn't think he would make it.
And Thor gets to be the hero to Asgard
Yeah it's kind of weird how after all that loki still gets to live.
Right.  Does Asgard even want Loki back?  Probably not.
Yeah that's the one thing I don't really like about super hero series they're too soft on the guys trying to destroy the world.
They let them live to torment again!
Gotta keep that cash flow coming in can't write them off you might need them for a sequel!
Very true.  Keep the movies coming.  Marvel is good at that.
Did the tesseract ever come up again?  I don't remember if it was relevant in any of the other movies.
Nope I think that was the end of that story line.
At least as far as I can remember.
I think we've had 3 conversations with the third paragraph that came up does that count as the 4th or something?  I don't know if we're supposed to click finish conversation now or not or something.
I wondered the same thing.
We could probably try.  I think we just had to respond 15 times total?
I think it was 12 total I think we should be good.
Okay!  Take care!
See ya mate.
